               <msContents>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 9; Nelson collection no. N263.  The scribe Esminis was responsible for many other price of oil receipts from Thebes between years 30 and 38 of Ptolemy II.  (See additional OIM ostraca.)  1/2 silver [kite] 1/2 obol or 1 1/2 obols is the price of 3/4 kotule or 0.20 liter of oil.  1/2 obol is the price of 1/4 kotule or 0.07 liter of oil.  Thus, a total of 2 obols were paid for a total of 1 kotule or 0.27 liter of oil.</note>
                     <note type="general">Location: Oriental Institute</note>
