                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The writing of the season name in line 3 is clearly peret because the curved third sign is the complementary r group.  The shorter writing of the season name in line 4 must therefore be shemw, which also gives a logical sequence of dates.  In line 4, the top of the sn sign appears to be ligatured to the t sign (for sn.t, "sister").</p>
